<subSubSection id="DC20B5751CC41D74356659F8126BE1C0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="229F3A92F0F8CF11442C17210EEC0934" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A24C25B5B143B9FD2B81CF37204A6F5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Mexico (Veracruz), in oak-pine forest, tropical moist forest, or cloud forest, often in disturbed or secondary forest, in shady canyons and ravines, 1750-2600 m in elevation (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="08682A081F57B76CA8D132854D1E8B7D" captionStart="Figure 65" captionStartId="F65" captionText="Figure 65. Map of geographic distribution of L. michaelneei based on herbarium specimen data." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.168.51904.figure65" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/480077" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">65</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="FEE6CBDFA2F46BAF1A0AF71DEB26FFD3" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.168.51904.figure65" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/480077" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 65" startId="F65">
